  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uganda: Empowering Orphans to Become Entrepreneurs</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will equip 50 orphans and vulnerable children affected by HIV &amp; AIDS with the tools necessary to start health-nourishing, income-generating, sustainable farms. We will provide these children with crop seedlings, farm equipment, bicycles, rainwater harvesters and business skills to start their farms and renew their livelihood. We plan to ensure the sustainability of this project by using a percentage of the profit from each group of orphans to fund the succeeding groups&apos; tools.</narrative>
  </description>
